Drop `testonly = true` from the in-process GPU command-buffer components so the
(non-testonly) miniblink_host library can use them for WebGL.

gpu/ipc:gl_in_process_context (GLInProcessContext + InProcessCommandBuffer +
GpuInProcessThreadService) and gpu/ipc:gpu_thread_holder (InProcessGpuThreadHolder)
are the simplest way to run an in-process GPU command buffer over ANGLE/SwiftShader —
the backend blink's WebGL provider consumes. They are marked testonly by upstream
POLICY (intended for tests), but ALL their deps are non-testonly and their only
"test" file (test_gpu_thread_holder.cc) pulls just base/no_destructor.h — so removing
the marker yields a sound non-testonly build. This is a standalone-embedder adaptation
(we own this tree); no source/behavior change, only target visibility.

diff --git a/gpu/ipc/BUILD.gn b/gpu/ipc/BUILD.gn
index aa04b6b..eedf1c3 100644
--- a/gpu/ipc/BUILD.gn
+++ b/gpu/ipc/BUILD.gn
@@ -5,8 +5,6 @@
 import("//build/config/ui.gni")
 
 component("gl_in_process_context") {
-  testonly = true
-
   sources = [
     "gl_in_process_context.cc",
     "gl_in_process_context.h",
@@ -47,8 +45,6 @@ component("gl_in_process_context") {
 }
 
 component("gpu_thread_holder") {
-  testonly = true
-
   sources = [
     "in_process_gpu_thread_holder.cc",
     "in_process_gpu_thread_holder.h",
